cs.CR, cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.SE, cs.NI 

Reasoning: 
- cs.CR (Cryptography and Security) is the most likely category as the paper focuses on detecting malicious attacks in Cyber-Physical Systems. 
- cs.SY (Systems and Control) is also likely as the paper discusses the performance of different anomaly detection schemes on a real-world platform. 
- cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) is a possible category as the paper describes methods to measure the capability of an attacker and to design a detector that can achieve a user-specified rate of false alarms, which involves machine learning techniques. 
- cs.SE (Software Engineering) is a possible category as the paper discusses the design and evaluation of a Dynamic Watermarking detector. 
- cs.NI (Networking and Internet Architecture) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with detecting attacks in Cyber-Physical Systems, which may involve networked devices.
